What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Low Voltage Energy Distribution Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Low Voltage Energy Distribution Market

The low voltage energy distribution market is expected to witness market growth at a rate of 6.70% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028 is expected to reach USD 1,57,003.73 million by 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on low voltage energy distribution market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecast period while providing their impacts on the market’s growth. The rise in global electricity demand is escalating the growth of low voltage energy distribution market.

Low voltage network or secondary network refers to the system of network which is utilized to carry current from transformer to the electric meter of individual users and generally operated at low voltage level. The purpose of the low voltage energy distribution is offering protection and safety to the building. These low voltage energy distributions are extensively used in applications such as commercial sites, industrial sites and power plants among others.

The rise in need for the protection of electrical devices and network components acts as one of the major factors driving the growth of low voltage energy distribution market. The rise in access to electricity, increase in the number of construction and infrastructural activities across the globe and adoption of smart grid technology accelerate the low voltage energy distribution market growth. The growth in rural energy demand, high access to electricity and the rise in issues with the aging power infrastructure further influence the low voltage energy distribution market. Additionally, growth in population, increase in energy demand globally, research and development and surge in investment positively affect the low voltage energy distribution market. Furthermore, technological advancement and growth of renewable power generation extend profitable opportunities to the low voltage energy distribution market players in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

On the other hand, high cost associated with the larger conductor required to transmit high current and issues with the product failures are the major factors expected to obstruct the low voltage energy distribution market growth. The rise in concerns regarding high voltage drop and low efficiency is projected to challenge the low voltage energy distribution market in the forecast period of 2021-2028.

